HEADWORD: Reamer
<hw>Ream"er</hw> <pr>(-⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who, or
that which, reams; specifically, an instrument with cutting or scraping
edges, used, with a twisting motion, for enlarging a round hole, as the
bore of a cannon, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

